ZH: 水手正在修理船上的绳索。
EN: The sailors are repairing the ropes on the boat.

ZH: 那个水手是十分有经验的船长。
EN: That sailor is a very experienced captain.

ZH: 水手们在大海上等待风浪的到来。
EN: The sailors are waiting for the arrival of the storm at sea.

ZH: 这艘船上的水手们都是年轻人。
EN: The sailors on this ship are all young people.

ZH: 水手们正在准备下海收获鱼类。
EN: The sailors are preparing to go to sea to catch fish.

ZH: 那位水手的妻子常常会担心他的安全。
EN: The sailor's wife often worries about his safety.

ZH: 水手们在船上进行定期的维护工作。
EN: The sailors are carrying out regular maintenance work on the ship.

ZH: 那个年轻水手刚刚加入了这支船队。
EN: That young sailor has just joined this fleet.

ZH: 水手们要准备好面对任何突发情况。
EN: The sailors must be prepared to face any unexpected situation.

ZH: 这个海港里停靠着许多船只，上面的水手们都很忙碌。
EN: Many ships are docked in this harbor, and the sailors on board are very busy.

ZH: 水手们必须迅速行动来避免船只与其他船只相撞。
EN: The sailors must act quickly to avoid collisions with other ships.

ZH: 水手们需要有耐心和勇气来应对各种挑战。
EN: The sailors need patience and courage to face various challenges.

ZH: 水手们在船上工作时总是穿着统一的工作服。
EN: The sailors always wear uniforms when working on the ship.

ZH: 那位老水手已经在船上工作了三十年。
EN: The old sailor has been working on the ship for thirty years.

ZH: 水手们靠航海技能来指引他们的航行方向。
EN: The sailors rely on their navigation skills to guide their direction of sailing.

ZH: 水手们每天都要检查船只的安全状况。
EN: The sailors check the safety condition of the ship every day.

ZH: 小组的领头水手负责指挥团队完成任务。
EN: The lead sailor of the group is responsible for directing the team to complete the task.

ZH: 水手们需要保持良好的体力和健康状态。
EN: Sailors need to maintain good physical strength and health.

ZH: 水手们在船上遇到恶劣天气时必须保持镇定。
EN: Sailors must remain calm when encountering bad weather at sea.

ZH: 每一位水手都对自己在海上的表现负有责任。
EN: Every sailor is responsible for their performance at sea.
